@node "Window" "Window"
@next "Preferences"
@prev "Menus"


 @{fg highlight}Short:@{fg text}

  Is the only mandatory field, and has to be in the first
  line. It lets you specify a 40 character description of your
  upload, that will be seen and INDEX and RECENT so everyone
  can easily learn about your upload. Don't repeat the file
  name here, but if several versions of your archive exist,
  specify the version number here. Try to explain what the
  program *does*. Music should specify the style.

 @{fg highlight}Uploader:@{fg text}

  Lets you indicate your email address so we can contact you
  if something goes wrong (and this happens more often than
  you think). Please always provide it.

 @{fg highlight}Author:@{fg text}

  Is the place where you can indicate who created the piece of
  software you uploaded.

 @{fg highlight}Type:@{fg text}

  Is the place where you can propose a directory where the file
  should be moved. Check the file TREE for possible subdirs.

 @{fg highlight}Replaces:@{fg text}

  Lets you specify files that are superseded by your upload.
  Give full path, e.g. biz/patch/PageStreamPatch*

 @{fg highlight}Version:@{fg text}

  The version number of your upload. Don't use version
  numbers in files names if possible.

 @{fg highlight}Distribution:@{fg text}

  Lets you specify where your upload is OK to distribute.
  If you specify the 'NoCD' keyword here, your upload will
  not appear on the CD's made of this site. If you specify
  'Aminet', you only give Aminet the distribution permission.

 @{fg highlight}Edit Description Text:@{fg text}

  Run external text editor.This Text added to the end of readme file.
  After end of editing select @{b}@{u}Save and Exit@{ub}@{uu}.

 @{fg highlight}Source Dir:@{fg text}

  Drawer with your program.This drawer will be packed with Lha.

 @{fg highlight}Archive Name:@{fg text}

  Name of output Lha and readme files.(If specified foo name, then
  program create two file foo.readme and foo.lha).

 @{fg highlight}S:@{fg text}

  Popup asl requester for source dir select.

 @{fg highlight}Readme and Pack <-> Only Readme:@{fg text}

  Readme and Pack - create two files .radme and .lha.

  Only Readme     - create only .readme file.

 @{fg highlight}Ok:@{fg text}

  Start files creating.
@endnode

@node "Preferences" "Preferences"
@next "Bugs&Errors"
@prev "Window"

 @{fg highlight}Lha:@{fg text}

  This string specified external Lha program.

  lha a -x "outname" "inname1" "inname2" .....

  |       |
  \________\_You can change only this place in string.

 @{fg highlight}Ed:@{fg text}

  This string specified external Editor program.

  Ed filename

  | |
  \_\_You can change only this place in string.

 @{fg highlight}Uploader/Author:@{fg text}

  This listview show the list of uploaders and authors.

 @{fg highlight}Type:@{fg text}

  Show list of dirs.

 @{fg highlight}Add:@{fg text}

  Add item to list.

 @{fg highlight}Delete:@{fg text}

  Delete item from list.

 @{fg highlight}Save:@{fg text}

  Exit from prefs with saving.

 @{fg highlight}Use:@{fg text}

  Exit with prefs using.

 @{fg highlight}Cancel:@{fg text}

  Exit without saving.
@endnode

@node "Bugs&Errors" "Bugs&Errors"
@next "History"
@prev "Preferences"

 @{fg highlight}Bugs@{fg text}

  Not bugs found at this time.

 @{fg highlight}Errors@{fg text}

  If program don't work or exit and all strings set correctly, that
  means:

   @{fg highlight}*@{fg text} No memory available.

   @{fg highlight}*@{fg text} Ed and Lha strings not set correctly  in prefs.

   @{fg highlight}*@{fg text} Errors associate with Ed or Lha program.

  All other situation is bugs.
@endnode

